cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper is about detecting machine-translated text, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method that uses similarity between intrinsic text and back-translation, which involves machine learning techniques such as feature extraction and classification. This suggests that the paper could also fit under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves text classification, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
